 and sometimes idiosyncratic techniques that scholars and readers developed in an era of new technology and exploding information.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBibliographyzEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aBibliographyzEuropexHistoryy17th century. 0aCommunication in learning and scholarshipzEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aCommunication in learning and scholarshipzEuropexHistoryy17th century. 0aEncyclopedias and dictionarieszEuropexHistory and criticism. 0aEncyclopedias and dictionaries, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aNote-takingxHistory. 0aReference booksxHistory. 0aReference books, LatinzEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aReference books, LatinzEuropexHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300168495423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300168495.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles